==Esperanto==

===Etymology===
Demonstratives from English ([[this]]), Bosnian (''[[ti]]''), Dutch (''[[dit]]''), German (''[[dies]]''), Polish (''[[ten]]''), Russian ([[те]])

===Affix===
[[Category:Esperanto prefixes]]
'''ti-'''
# this-, that-. (Demonstrative correlative prefix.)

===Derived terms===
* ''[[tiu]]'': '''that''' individual
* ''[[tio]]'': '''that''' [object]
* ''[[tia]]'': '''that''' kind of
* ''[[ties]]'': belonging to '''that'''
* ''[[tiel]]'': '''that''' manner/degree
* ''[[tie]]'': '''that''' place, [[there]]
* ''[[tiam]]'': '''that''' time, [[then]]
* ''[[tiom]]'': '''that''' quantity
* ''[[tial]]'': '''that''' reason, [[therefore]]